#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:5.1"
msgid "25. Cīvaraacchindanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "25. The training rule on taking robe(-cloth) back"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.25.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.139"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2336"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.2"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhātuno saddhivihārikaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Just then Venerable Upananda the Sakyan said to his brother’s student,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.4"
msgid "“ehāvuso, janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, let’s go wandering in the country.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.5"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, gamissāmi;"
msgstr "“I can’t go, Venerable,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.6"
msgid "dubbalacīvaromhī”ti."
msgstr "my robes are worn.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.7"
msgid "“Ehāvuso, ahaṃ te cīvaraṃ dassāmī”ti"
msgstr "“I’ll give you a robe.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.8"
msgid "tassa cīvaraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "And he gave him a robe."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.9"
msgid "Assosi kho so bhikkhu—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that monk heard"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.10"
msgid "“bhagavā kira janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti."
msgstr "that the Master was about to go wandering in the country."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.11"
msgid "Atha kho tassa bhikkhuno etadahosi—"
msgstr "He thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.12"
msgid "“na dānāhaṃ āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmi, bhagavatā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Now I won’t go wandering with Venerable Upananda, but with the Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then, when Upananda said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.14"
msgid "“ehi dāni, āvuso, janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Let’s go,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.15"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, tayā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmi, bhagavatā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "he replied, “I’m not going with you, but with the Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.16"
msgid "“Yampi tyāhaṃ, āvuso, cīvaraṃ adāsiṃ, mayā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti,"
msgstr "“Well, the robe I gave you is going with me,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.17"
msgid "kupito anattamano acchindi."
msgstr "and angry and displeased he just took it back."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.18"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "That monk informed other monks about what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.19"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "And the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.20"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:6.21"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda give away a robe and then take it back, angry and displeased?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.255"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2337"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.140"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted in this way?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him: “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.5"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you give a robe to a monk and then take it back, angry and displeased?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.6"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:7.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:8.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2338"></a>
#. <strong class="rule">
#. <span class="note" hidden><i lang="pli">Cīvara</i> means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context. Sometimes, such as here, it means both, and I then render it as robe(-cloth).</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:8.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindeyya vā acchindāpeyya vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk himself gives a robe(-cloth) to a monk, but then, angry and displeased, takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:8.3"
msgid "(<em>25</em>:<strong>44</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:9.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:9.2"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:9.3"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:9.4"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:9.5"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:9.6"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2340"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:10.1"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr "To a monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:10.2"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "to another monk."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2341"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:11.1"
msgid "Sāmanti"
msgstr "Himself:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:11.2"
msgid "sayaṃ datvā."
msgstr "he himself has given it."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2342"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:12.1"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe(-cloth):"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, jute, and hemp; see <span class="ref">Mv.8.3.1</span>.</span>
#. <span class="note" hidden>This means not smaller than 8 by 4 <i lang="pli">sugata</i> finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see <span class="ref">Kkh. 94.4</span> and BMC I, pp. 565-566.</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:12.2"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ, vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robes(-cloth), but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2343"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:13.1"
msgid "Kupito anattamanoti"
msgstr "Angry and displeased:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:13.2"
msgid "anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "discontent, having hatred, hostile."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2344"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:14.1"
msgid "Acchindeyyāti"
msgstr "Takes […] back:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:14.2"
msgid "sayaṃ acchindati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "if he takes it back himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2345"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.1"
msgid "Acchindāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets […] taken back:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.2"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.3"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi acchindati, nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other takes back many times, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.4"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe(-cloth) should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in <a href=\"/en/pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.141"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.7"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ bhikkhussa sāmaṃ datvā acchinnaṃ nissaggiyaṃ imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe(-cloth) which I took back after giving it to a monk is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.8"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.9"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:15.10"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe(-cloth) back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:16.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2346"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:16.2"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained and he perceives him as fully ordained, and after giving him a robe(-cloth), angry and displeased, he takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:16.3"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and after giving him a robe(-cloth), angry and displeased, he takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:16.4"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, but he perceives him as not fully ordained, and after giving him a robe(-cloth), angry and displeased, he takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2347"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:17.1"
msgid "Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, after giving him another requisite, angry and displeased, he takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:17.2"
msgid "Anupasampannassa cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, after giving a robe(-cloth) or another requisite to a person who is not fully ordained, angry and displeased, he takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:17.3"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:17.4"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:17.5"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, and he perceives him as not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:18.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2348"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:18.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:18.3"
msgid "so vā deti,"
msgstr "if the other monk gives it back;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:18.4"
msgid "tassa vā vissasanto gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he takes it on trust from him;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:18.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:18.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2349"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:19.1"
msgid "Cīvaraacchindanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on taking robe(-cloth) back, is finished."

